### What Needs Your Cloudflare Access

**GitHub Pages HTTPS enforcement fails** because the SSL cert hasn't been provisioned:

```
curl -X PUT .../repos/SuperInstance/cocapn-ai-web/pages -d '{"https_enforced":true}'
→ 404 "The certificate does not exist yet"
```

This is NOT urgent — Cloudflare handles HTTPS termination on the front end, so users see HTTPS fine. But the GitHub Pages `html_url` shows `http://` instead of `https://`, which means:

1. Some crawlers/previewers might follow the HTTP URL
2. GitHub can't enforce HTTPS redirects on their side

### What to Do (when you have a moment)

1. Go to GitHub repo Settings → Pages → scroll to "Enforce HTTPS"
2. If the checkbox is there but unchecked, check it
3. If it says "certificate not yet provisioned" — wait 24-48 hours (GitHub auto-provisions after DNS verification)
4. If it still doesn't work after 48h, check that the DNS CNAME on Cloudflare points to `superinstance.github.io` (not an A record)

### Current DNS Setup (working)
- `plato.purplepincher.org` → Cloudflare proxy IPs (104.21.63.242, 172.67.173.93)
- Cloudflare → GitHub Pages backend
- HTTPS: Cloudflare terminates, backend connects over HTTP (proxy mode)

